01:03.296 --> 01:05.287
How's it lookin'?

01:06.900 --> 01:09.596
Here it comes. Get ready.

01:10.637 --> 01:12.628
Come on!
Ah!

01:17.577 --> 01:20.410
Okay, you're clear!

01:24.217 --> 01:29.917
Which way? Which way?
Which way? Which way?
Oh, boy.

02:43.630 --> 02:46.793
<i>[ Insects, Birds Chirping ]</i>
[ Panting ]

02:50.136 --> 02:53.367
What the hell you mean,
you don't know where we are?

02:53.439 --> 02:57.603
Well-
You said you grew up
around here.

02:57.677 --> 03:02.171
I did?
[ Grunts ] You-
You lied to me, didn't you?

03:02.248 --> 03:06.651
No. I- No, I didn't lie to ya.
I mean, I don't think I lied to ya.

03:06.719 --> 03:10.485
What you mean,
you don't think?
I mean- I mean, no.

03:10.557 --> 03:13.651
No. What?
<i>[ Dogs Barking In Distance ]</i>

03:13.726 --> 03:16.524
Damn that dog's nose!

03:18.665 --> 03:21.395
[ Sam Grunts ]
No. No. No.

03:21.467 --> 03:24.959
Look. Look. [ Panting ]
We can't outrun their noses.

03:25.038 --> 03:27.734
We have to.

03:27.807 --> 03:32.073
You can't hear 'em?
They gettin' closer.

03:34.914 --> 03:38.509
Maybe we should just
give ourselves up.
Say what?

03:38.585 --> 03:42.521
The only way we goin' back
to that camp now is in a pine box.

03:42.589 --> 03:45.888
[ Continues Panting ]

03:45.959 --> 03:48.826
[ Chittering ]

03:48.895 --> 03:51.227
Come on. Come on.

03:51.297 --> 03:55.256
What? No. No.
[ Grunts ]
Yes, yes, yes!

03:55.335 --> 03:58.168
[ Skunk Sprays ]
[ Sam Groans ]

03:59.405 --> 04:02.932
Mr. Dog can't smell us now.
Yeah, I know,

04:03.009 --> 04:05.239
but he can see us
and our footprints.

04:05.311 --> 04:08.439
Come here.

04:08.514 --> 04:11.745
Come on.
[ Grunts ]

04:11.818 --> 04:14.582
Come on.

04:14.654 --> 04:17.088
Uh, I ain't goin' in there.

04:17.156 --> 04:21.353
I ain't goin' in there!
It's either in there-
It's either in there or in a pine box.

04:21.427 --> 04:24.396
Now, come on. Come on.
No. I don't wanna go in there!

04:24.464 --> 04:27.592
I can't stand small spaces!
Let me go! Let me go!

04:27.667 --> 04:31.330
It's too small for me!
It's just for a little bit.
Now,just take it easy. Take it easy, Boone.

04:31.404 --> 04:36.000
Shh, shh. Easy, easy.
They're almost here. Shut up.

04:36.075 --> 04:40.307
- <i>[ Dogs Barking ]</i>
- <i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Come on, Demon. Come on, boy.</i>

04:40.380 --> 04:43.042
Hey, boss.
He's pickin' up skunk.

04:43.116 --> 04:46.449
<i>[ Barking Continues ]</i>

04:46.519 --> 04:49.454
- <i>Here, boy. Come here.</i>
- [ Dog Whimpering ]

04:49.522 --> 04:54.824
Good boy. We'll find them boys
before they get themselves hurt.

04:57.130 --> 05:00.463
[ Barking Ferociously ]
What you got, boy?

05:01.968 --> 05:04.994
- <i>[ Guard ] Lord, how can they</i>
<i>smell anything for that skunk?</i>
- <i>[ Guard #2 ] He's killing the scent.</i>

05:05.071 --> 05:08.165
<i>Let's move on.</i>

05:31.364 --> 05:33.832
[ Both Panting ]

05:35.735 --> 05:41.196
I've had about...
enough ofTalawaga County
as I ever wanna see.

05:41.274 --> 05:43.902
Oh, you always
been claustrophobic?

05:43.976 --> 05:49.107
I got too big a body
for tiny places...

05:49.182 --> 05:51.878
is what my mama always said.

05:51.951 --> 05:56.012
Outside is where I got to be.

05:56.089 --> 05:58.557
Anyplace else-

06:00.059 --> 06:02.584
I can't go back.

06:03.663 --> 06:06.029
[ Sighs ]

06:06.099 --> 06:08.294
[ Snores ]

06:08.368 --> 06:11.269
[ Device Beeping ]

06:11.337 --> 06:16.798
Gee, Sam, it kind of looks
like you're dressed up for hard times.

06:16.876 --> 06:19.777
This is the latest thing
in prison escapes.

06:19.846 --> 06:23.043
Yeah. Well,
it's more like a chain gang.

06:23.116 --> 06:25.983
Thank you, Dr. Watson.
Nothing to it.

06:26.052 --> 06:29.715
You're in 1 956,
November 2.

06:29.789 --> 06:33.316
Your name is Chance Terrence Cole,

06:33.393 --> 06:37.124
and you're a local, small-time pet-
<i>[ Beeping ]</i>

06:37.196 --> 06:41.155
- [ Squealing ]
-" Petty.'' Oh. Petty thief.

06:41.234 --> 06:45.136
You're a local petty thief,
and you passed some bad checks.
You're doin' nine months...

06:45.204 --> 06:47.968
in Ta-Ta- " Tawawawa.''

06:48.040 --> 06:50.167
Talawa-Talawaga.
What?

06:50.243 --> 06:55.840
- <i>Talawaga.</i>
- Talawawa County Prison road gang.
Whatever it is.

06:57.183 --> 07:00.914
And I'm really innocent, right?
And I'm here to prove
that this guy's not guilty, right?

07:00.987 --> 07:04.115
- No. Not exactly.
- No?

07:04.190 --> 07:06.920
<i>Ziggy checked the police files,</i>
<i>and you've got a rap sheet.</i>

07:06.993 --> 07:11.191
- What about him?
- <i>Uh,Jasper Boone is his name.</i>

07:11.264 --> 07:16.201
He's doin', uh, 1 5 big ones
for armed robbery and attempted murder...

07:16.269 --> 07:18.601
<i>in a town called Langston.</i>

07:18.671 --> 07:22.107
He hit a jewelry store
not long ago.
[ Beeping ]

07:22.175 --> 07:24.166
- Wonderful.
- Ziggy's still workin' on this...

07:24.243 --> 07:26.336
and tryin' to find out why you're here,
so I'll go check with him.

07:26.412 --> 07:29.210
<i>As soon as I hear something,</i>
<i>I'll come right away</i>
<i>and let you know.</i>

07:29.282 --> 07:31.546
- Thanks, Al.
- You know, it's funny.

07:31.617 --> 07:37.214
What?
If I wasn't a hologram,
I could swear I could smell skunk.

07:40.493 --> 07:45.226
<i>[ Water Gurgling ]</i>
<i>[ Boone ] My daddy was a colored farmer</i>
<i>from North Carolina.</i>

07:45.298 --> 07:50.133
My mama was a Muskogee.
Indian?

07:50.203 --> 07:53.468
Pureblood. Come on.

07:53.539 --> 07:56.531
[ Both Panting ]

07:57.944 --> 08:00.742
She and Pops...

08:03.015 --> 08:06.041
died when I was still little.

08:06.118 --> 08:11.784
A kerosene heater blew up,
so I went off-

08:11.858 --> 08:15.316
went off to live with my grandmama,
my mama's mama.

08:15.394 --> 08:17.658
[ Continues Panting ]

08:26.572 --> 08:29.666
- Whoa!
- Breakfast?

08:29.742 --> 08:32.073
I'm not real hungry right now.

08:33.679 --> 08:35.669
Me neither.

08:39.852 --> 08:41.979
You know,

08:44.190 --> 08:47.682
it was hard on the reservation...

08:47.760 --> 08:51.423
being <i>osonko,</i> half-breed.

08:51.497 --> 08:57.367
But out here,
they ain't got no rules, no honor.

08:57.436 --> 09:01.372
<i>They chain you up,</i>
<i>take away your hope,your spirit.</i>

09:01.440 --> 09:05.274
Well, that's what happens
when you break the law.

09:05.344 --> 09:07.744
I didn't break-
I didn't break any law.

09:07.813 --> 09:10.543
I didn't do anything!
Okay, okay, okay. Okay.

09:10.616 --> 09:13.847
I left home to find work.

09:13.920 --> 09:15.945
I'm on the bus,
so I get off at town...

09:16.022 --> 09:20.789
'cause I don't like being cooped up
in there too long.

09:20.860 --> 09:26.560
I walk into the store.
It has some pretty jewelry,
so I just look.

09:26.632 --> 09:30.295
Then I hear yellin',
and I hear a gunshot.

09:30.369 --> 09:33.031
Suddenly I'm pushed to the ground,
and somebody accused me...

09:33.105 --> 09:36.404
of shootin' and robbin' the man
that owned the store.

09:36.475 --> 09:40.639
I ain't never robbed nobody
in my life, Cole! And nobody believed me!

09:40.713 --> 09:43.443
Nobody listened!

09:45.484 --> 09:48.885
And then they locked me in.

09:52.258 --> 09:57.457
I was born outside.
I was raised outside.

09:59.432 --> 10:02.595
And for two months now,
they had me...

10:02.668 --> 10:07.367
chained up and shut in.

10:09.241 --> 10:11.903
But not anymore.

10:13.179 --> 10:16.342
Not anymore.
That's why you escaped?

10:16.415 --> 10:19.316
It was either that...

10:20.453 --> 10:22.444
or die.

10:22.521 --> 10:25.718
<i>[ Vehicle Approaching ]</i>

10:29.695 --> 10:32.687
We gotta find a way
to get out of these things.

10:46.912 --> 10:49.437
[ Dogs Barking ]

11:05.965 --> 11:09.196
Look for a saw, a hammer
or anything, right?

11:09.268 --> 11:12.260
Okay. Wait a second.

11:13.739 --> 11:17.004
How about this?
Perfect.

11:17.076 --> 11:19.670
All we need i- is this.

11:25.518 --> 11:27.509
[ Straining ]

11:30.456 --> 11:32.549
Give me the ax.

11:32.625 --> 11:35.287
Put your hand up.

11:37.096 --> 11:39.963
Okay. Do mine. Come on.

11:41.901 --> 11:44.597
Yeah.
Oh.

11:44.670 --> 11:47.537
Next stop, Louisiana!

11:49.575 --> 11:52.169
<i>[ Al ]</i>
<i>You can't let him go, Sam.</i>

11:55.114 --> 11:58.345
He says he didn't do it.
Are you tellin' me he did?

11:58.417 --> 12:04.083
Yeah, I know, but, see,
Ziggy says there's a 98.6% chance
that he's innocent.

12:04.156 --> 12:09.059
Even while Boone's
been in prison, there's been some guy
robbing jewelry stores...

12:09.128 --> 12:12.063
using the same M.O.,
exactly the same one every time.

12:12.131 --> 12:15.931
And there's been
five robberies.

12:17.970 --> 12:20.962
So the real robber's
still on the outside?
<i>[ Al ] You got it.</i>

12:21.040 --> 12:23.634
- <i>Come on, Cole. Come on.</i>
- Yeah.

12:26.846 --> 12:32.011
And an innocent guy's gonna spend the next
1 5 years on a Mississippi chain gang?
Actually, no.

12:32.084 --> 12:35.520
Then he gets cleared?
No. Not exactly.

12:35.588 --> 12:39.854
In about five minutes,
he runs out of this barn...

12:39.925 --> 12:42.018
and gets shot trying to escape.

12:50.236 --> 12:52.966
[ Dogs Barking ]

12:56.142 --> 12:58.474
<i>[ Chatter ]</i>

13:05.417 --> 13:08.011
Was the real robber
ever caught?
Uh, negative.

13:08.087 --> 13:10.419
All right. Look.
You gotta find out
who the real guy is, all right?

13:10.489 --> 13:13.652
Then get me the information
so I can get it to the people
who can do something about it.

13:13.726 --> 13:16.422
Yeah, and if I had blonde hair
and I could sing,
I'd be Madonna.

13:16.495 --> 13:18.895
Time to be goin'. Come on.
No, no. Wait a second. Wait a second.

13:18.964 --> 13:21.455
I'm not so sure
that's a good idea.
I ain't waitin' in here till dark.

13:21.534 --> 13:24.230
That's another seven or eight hours.
Hey, Sam.

13:24.303 --> 13:27.739
Ziggy says there's gonna be
another robbery tonight in Kerrville.

13:27.807 --> 13:31.299
Good.
No, it ain't. I can't take
it in here much longer.

13:31.377 --> 13:33.572
You guys have gotta hide out
or go back.

13:33.646 --> 13:36.740
What are our chances?
We ain't got no chance
unless we move!

13:36.816 --> 13:38.841
All right. All right.
Listen to me.Just-

13:38.918 --> 13:41.648
<i>Your chances are less than 50-50,</i>
<i>and they're goin'down.</i>

13:42.721 --> 13:45.690
See if you can get rid
of the dogs.
I'll find someplace to hide.

13:45.758 --> 13:48.192
Okay. Okay. I'm gone.

13:52.464 --> 13:55.024
[ Dogs Barking ]
[ Guards Chattering ]

13:55.100 --> 14:00.868
Hey, doggie, doggie, doggie!
Name that chicken flavor.
Right this way!

14:00.940 --> 14:03.374
What those dogs up to?
Maybe they backtracked.

14:03.442 --> 14:06.843
[ Yelping ]
They must've seen a rabbit
or something!

14:06.912 --> 14:09.005
Come on, Cole!

14:09.081 --> 14:11.481
Wait a second. Wait a second.
Listen to me. Listen to me.

14:11.550 --> 14:14.781
I think we should stay in here
and just hide for a while. All right?
What? And wait for winter?

14:14.854 --> 14:19.018
No. No. I got a bad feelin' about this,
Boone. I don't know what it is. I can't-
You got a bad feelin'?

14:19.091 --> 14:22.720
Yes.
How you think you gonna be feelin'
if you wind up in a cockfight, huh?

14:24.296 --> 14:27.197
[ Exhales ]
Boy, if I'd have known I had
to do this much running,

14:27.266 --> 14:29.291
<i>I would've</i>
<i>worn my cross-training shoes.</i>

14:29.368 --> 14:33.395
What happened to you, huh?
Yesterday you couldn't wait
to get out.

14:33.472 --> 14:36.134
You kept tellin' me
how if you had to spend another year-
Another year?

14:36.208 --> 14:41.145
- <i>[Jasper ] Yeah. You was gonna go crazy.</i>
- Wait a minute. Ziggy says you're only
supposed to be here for nine months.

14:41.213 --> 14:43.704
<i>Here it is.</i>
<i>You got a nine-month sentence...</i>

14:43.782 --> 14:47.582
starting on July 3, 1 954.

14:47.653 --> 14:49.917
I've been in here two years?
I can't take it, Cole!

14:49.989 --> 14:53.254
<i>I can't.! Now, two months</i>
<i>is more than I can stand.!</i>

14:53.325 --> 14:57.455
If you wanna go back,
give yourself up, go on.
I won't stop you.

14:57.529 --> 15:00.225
<i>But if you think</i>
<i>that I'm goin'back</i>-

15:01.233 --> 15:03.758
Damn! Damn!

15:03.836 --> 15:06.134
Sam, he's goin' out!
He's goin' out!

15:10.009 --> 15:12.102
Come on, Sam.

15:12.177 --> 15:16.944
Boone.
They're gonna kill you.
I'm gonna die in there anyway.

15:17.016 --> 15:20.611
No. No, Boone.
Listen to me, Boone.
Boone!

15:20.686 --> 15:23.849
Oh!
What? What happened?

15:25.057 --> 15:28.083
Sam- Oh, good.

15:28.160 --> 15:31.652
Take that stick,
bonk him on the head. Now!

15:31.730 --> 15:35.791
[ Grunts ]
What you doin', man?

15:35.868 --> 15:38.462
Just tryin' to save your life.

15:38.537 --> 15:43.270
With a club?
No. With my foot.

15:44.610 --> 15:49.547
Oh, good.
Now, do something.
Stick him in there. Yeah, yeah.

15:51.583 --> 15:55.417
Where are you gonna go?
Oh, good. Get in with him.
Good. Good.

15:57.456 --> 16:00.391
<i>[ Rifle Cocks ]</i>
Now, keep quiet. Oh.

16:00.459 --> 16:02.654
<i>Here comes one of the goons, Sam.</i>
<i>He's got a shotgun.</i>

16:02.728 --> 16:06.129
<i>Quiet in there.</i>

16:06.198 --> 16:08.166
[ Panting ]

16:08.233 --> 16:11.134
<i>[ Stifled Yelp ]</i>

16:12.805 --> 16:15.365
They're not here,
you little worm.

16:15.441 --> 16:19.309
- [ Sam Grunts ]
- [ Gunshot ]

16:19.378 --> 16:22.643
Mr. Monroe,
leave that boy alone.
[ Guards Chattering ]

16:22.715 --> 16:25.843
You'll have to excuse Mr. Monroe
here. He's a little cranky.
He's been up all night.

16:25.918 --> 16:30.014
All right, Sam. That's great.
Now, the rest is gonna
be a cakewalk.

16:30.089 --> 16:35.322
I'm gonna go back
and see if I can spot the robber.
Take it easy, will you?

16:35.394 --> 16:39.421
You boys sure are rough on jewelry.
Fortunately we can fix that.

16:42.334 --> 16:44.666
Oh, boy.

16:58.650 --> 17:01.915
I'm real disappointed in you,
Cole.

17:01.987 --> 17:04.580
I expected you to set an example...

17:04.656 --> 17:08.387
for the young'uns...
like Boone here.

17:08.460 --> 17:11.623
Guess I got
a little carried away.

17:13.799 --> 17:17.359
Take care of it.
Yes, sir.

17:17.435 --> 17:20.064
<i>Them the boys that run off?</i>

17:20.138 --> 17:23.836
Well, you could say
they took an unplanned vacation.

17:23.909 --> 17:28.107
Well, I guess
they're back in school now.

17:28.180 --> 17:32.139
See ya tomorrow, Cool.
See ya around,Jake.

17:33.485 --> 17:38.354
- <i>[ Engine Starts ]</i>
- I swear I won't run again, boss.

17:38.424 --> 17:43.521
- I swear on my mama's grave.
- Cole, you been here the longest.

17:43.595 --> 17:46.758
You get to call it.
Call it.

17:52.204 --> 17:54.195
Tails.

17:59.511 --> 18:02.071
- Tails it is.
- No!

18:02.147 --> 18:04.138
Sorry, Boone.
No!
Come on, boy.

18:04.216 --> 18:08.482
I swear I won't run again!
Just don't throw me in there!

18:08.554 --> 18:13.514
Hey, I ain't doin' nothin'
to ya, Boonie boy. Your partner here's
the one who called it.

18:13.592 --> 18:18.620
- If anybody's to blame, he is.
- Cole. Cole. Don't do this to me, Cole. Please.

18:18.697 --> 18:24.192
<i>Mr. Cooley, sir,</i>
<i>I'll do the cockfights.</i>

18:24.269 --> 18:27.864
- <i>Anything. Cole?</i>
- You can't put him in there.
He's got claustrophobia.

18:27.940 --> 18:29.771
You can't-
Watch your hands, boy.

18:29.842 --> 18:32.310
Cole!
Get in there and stay.
Come on.

18:32.377 --> 18:34.368
<i>Cole.!</i>

18:34.446 --> 18:36.607
Please.

18:36.682 --> 18:41.381
Sorry, but I got something else
in mind for you, boy.

18:49.128 --> 18:52.996
<i>[ Sam Narrating ]</i>
<i>Each time Boone howled,</i>
<i>my stomach sank a little lower.</i>

18:53.065 --> 18:57.001
<i>[ Boone Howling ]</i>
<i>For him,</i>
<i>the pit was truly hell.</i>

18:57.069 --> 19:00.664
<i>And his only hope</i>
<i>for deliverance was Al.</i>

19:01.740 --> 19:04.573
<i>[ Howling Continues ]</i>

19:08.647 --> 19:11.775
[ Grunting, Groaning ]

19:11.850 --> 19:17.186
<i>[ Cooley ]</i>
<i>"For each ecstatic instant,</i>
<i>we must in anguish pay...</i>

19:17.256 --> 19:20.419
"in keen and quivering ratio...

19:20.492 --> 19:23.552
to the ecstasy.''

19:24.930 --> 19:28.491
[ Sam ]
I doubt that Emily Dickinson
had that in mind when she wrote that.

19:28.567 --> 19:31.400
[ Sighs ]
Yeah.
I doubt she did either.

19:32.771 --> 19:35.934
You and Boone
made me look bad today, boy.

19:36.008 --> 19:39.409
- Please don't do it again,
or I'll kill ya.
- You're killin' him now.

19:39.478 --> 19:42.879
<i>Maybe you got more spunk than</i>
<i>you should. Maybe you shouldjust...</i>

19:42.948 --> 19:47.476
<i>take these barrels back</i>
<i>to where you got 'em.</i>

19:47.553 --> 19:49.544
Night.

19:50.956 --> 19:54.221
<i>[ Al ]</i>
<i>Geez, Sam. What are they giving you</i>
<i>to eat here? Roadkill?</i>

19:55.360 --> 19:57.385
[ Groans ]
<i>Did you find him, Al?</i>

19:57.462 --> 20:00.056
- Who?
- The guy. Did you find the guy?

20:00.132 --> 20:02.566
The guy? Oh, yeah. The guy.
Yeah. I found the guy.

20:02.634 --> 20:05.762
He's a tall guy.
He's got dark hair.

20:05.837 --> 20:10.274
And get this: He puts makeup
on his face to make him look
like he's a black guy.

20:10.342 --> 20:14.210
Yeah. His name is Jake Wiles,

20:14.279 --> 20:17.077
and he works
for his family's grocery outfit.

20:17.149 --> 20:19.117
He drives a truck.
Jake Wiles?

20:19.184 --> 20:21.550
Wiles. Yeah.
<i>Wait a second.</i>
<i>He was here today.</i>

20:21.620 --> 20:23.247
He made a delivery here today.

20:23.322 --> 20:25.449
He was here today?

20:25.524 --> 20:27.822
[ Muttering ]

20:27.893 --> 20:30.259
What are you do-
Where are you going, Sam?

20:30.329 --> 20:32.320
To tell Boone.

20:35.567 --> 20:37.865
[ Chains Clanking ]

20:39.571 --> 20:41.903
Boone?

20:41.974 --> 20:44.340
[ Chains Clanking ]

20:46.645 --> 20:49.637
Boone? Boone?

20:49.715 --> 20:51.706
[ Choking ]

20:51.783 --> 20:54.479
- I'm gonna kill you.
- Boone, let him go!

20:54.553 --> 20:58.387
[ Choking ] Boone, listen to me.
I can get ya out of here...

20:58.457 --> 21:01.017
and not just the pit.

21:01.093 --> 21:03.960
I can get ya out-
out of prison.

21:04.029 --> 21:05.963
I know who did the robbery.

21:06.031 --> 21:10.525
- You're lying.
- Sam, tell him more! Give him the facts!
Tell him about the guy in the truck!

21:10.602 --> 21:15.369
<i>Let him go, Boone.!</i>
His name is Jake Wiles.
He drives the grocery truck.

21:15.440 --> 21:20.343
He makes himself up to look black-
to look black.

21:20.412 --> 21:22.471
[ Coughing ]
[ Panting ]

21:24.716 --> 21:27.844
How's that gonna
get me free, huh?

21:27.919 --> 21:30.479
[ Coughing ]
We'll tell the police.

21:30.555 --> 21:34.184
- What if they don't believe us?
- [ Wheezing ]

21:36.962 --> 21:39.328
Then I'll help ya escape.

21:39.398 --> 21:41.298
- [ Al ] Look out, Sam!
- [ Grunts ]

21:41.366 --> 21:44.893
I don't think that'd
be such a good idea, boy.

21:44.970 --> 21:47.404
Throw him in the pit.
Yes, sir.
Fun time, boys.

21:48.640 --> 21:51.006
<i>"Throw him in the pit'"?</i>

21:51.076 --> 21:54.671
It stinks in there, boy.

21:54.746 --> 21:58.978
[ Al ]
Don't put him in there. Hey!

22:03.088 --> 22:06.683
- Nighty night.
- Nighty night, ya slimes! Scum!

22:06.758 --> 22:12.697
<i>[ Muffled Speech ]</i>
<i>[ Boone ] Mr. Cooley boss.!</i>
<i>Let us out ofhere.!</i>

22:15.467 --> 22:18.493
<i>Cooley.! Boss Cooley.!</i>

22:19.971 --> 22:21.962
<i>Boss Cooley.!</i>

22:40.559 --> 22:44.086
<i>[ Al ]</i>
<i>Sam,you okay? How you feel?</i>
[ Grunts ]

22:44.162 --> 22:46.756
Not so good, huh?
I don't blame ya.

22:46.832 --> 22:49.528
Whoa!

22:58.977 --> 23:01.707
[ Horn Honking ]

23:01.780 --> 23:04.977
Come on! Out of the way!

23:05.050 --> 23:08.850
[ Horn Honks ]
Boone, what do you want?

23:08.920 --> 23:12.651
[ Sam ]
Boone, no! No, Boone!
[ Horn Honks ]

23:12.724 --> 23:15.056
- Boone!
- [ Both Muttering Angrily ]

23:15.127 --> 23:18.426
- [ Sam ] Boone!
- He's gonna kill that guy!

23:18.497 --> 23:20.965
[ All Yelling ]

23:21.032 --> 23:23.830
- [ Boone Yelps ]
- Come on, Boone.

23:23.902 --> 23:27.804
Get on back, boy.
Get out of it.
[ Chattering ]

23:32.711 --> 23:36.010
Can't remember when one ol' boy
caused so much trouble.
He's crazy.

23:36.081 --> 23:41.451
<i>He tried to kill me.!</i>
I don't belong here, Warden.

23:41.520 --> 23:43.454
Tell 'em.

23:43.522 --> 23:48.186
<i>Tell 'em you robbed that store</i>
<i>and shot that man in Langston.</i>

23:48.260 --> 23:51.195
I didn't shoot nobody!
I don't know what you're talkin' about!

23:51.263 --> 23:54.027
You're making some
mighty serious accusations here,
Boone.

23:54.099 --> 23:57.660
You got anything like proof?
I don't believe this.
You gonna listen to him?

23:57.736 --> 24:01.035
Well, do you?

24:01.106 --> 24:06.043
<i>This must be Warden Elias.</i>
<i>He's the closest thing to a cop</i>
<i>you're gonna find here.</i>

24:06.111 --> 24:10.343
He robbed a store in Kerrville last night,
the same way he did in Langston.

24:10.415 --> 24:14.476
Or at least that's what I heard
he was gonna do.

24:14.553 --> 24:17.989
Warden, I don't think
you should listen-
Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

24:24.429 --> 24:26.989
And how would you know that?

24:27.065 --> 24:31.001
If you don't believe me,
why don't you just talk to the sheriff
in Kerrville? Ask him.

24:33.538 --> 24:36.837
That's about enough sass
out of you, boy.

24:38.677 --> 24:40.668
What a slime.

24:42.314 --> 24:44.612
Put 'em both on the road crew
with the rest of'em.

24:44.683 --> 24:48.676
I want that pipe
out at Bellemeade Crossin' laid
and finished by the weekend.

24:48.753 --> 24:52.086
- Yes, sir.
- [ Guards Chattering ]

24:54.259 --> 24:56.625
Move it on out. Come on!

25:00.699 --> 25:04.635
I got Ziggy workin'
on a bunch of scenarios.

25:04.703 --> 25:08.605
We gotta find a way
for you to get the truth
to the right people.

25:08.673 --> 25:12.871
In the meantime,
you and Boone have gotta-
I know what we gotta do.

25:12.944 --> 25:17.608
We gotta escape.
You wanna sit around and run scenarios?

25:17.682 --> 25:20.310
You figure out how we're gonna
get outta here, all right?

25:20.385 --> 25:23.218
All right, all right, all right.

25:23.288 --> 25:27.622
Talkin' to yourself again, boy?
I'm startin' to worry about you, boy.
Come on.

25:37.469 --> 25:41.735
Tell me, Boone.
You talkin' to the man in the moon
last night?

25:41.806 --> 25:44.604
Is that what all that howlin'
was about?

25:44.676 --> 25:47.543
He the one
that told you that crazy story
aboutJake? Hmm?

25:47.612 --> 25:51.912
Yeah. Twenty years
is a long time in prison, Boone,

25:51.983 --> 25:54.315
especially this here one.

25:54.386 --> 25:56.411
His sentence is only for 1 5 years.

25:59.391 --> 26:04.294
His sentence <i>was</i> 1 5 years, boy,
just like yours <i>was</i> nine months.

26:04.362 --> 26:06.922
You bastard.

26:06.998 --> 26:11.833
<i>I hear a discouragin'word,</i>
<i>maybe another year in here'll</i>
<i>help teach you some better manners.</i>

26:11.903 --> 26:15.100
- How long you think
you can get away with this?
- You know, I had you figured...

26:15.173 --> 26:17.733
for a much smarter man
than this, Cole.

26:17.809 --> 26:21.245
See, this here prison road farm's
a long way from court.

26:21.313 --> 26:23.508
'Bout as far away from a court
as you ever gonna get, boy.

26:23.582 --> 26:27.848
Out here, nobody knows
what's goin' on.

26:27.919 --> 26:29.910
Nobody cares.

26:32.591 --> 26:34.957
<i>[ Insect Buzzing ]</i>

26:37.762 --> 26:40.925
[ Prisoners Coughing ]
<i>[ Bird Squawks ]</i>

26:40.999 --> 26:44.992
Well, unless we sprout wings,
we gonna die here now.

26:45.070 --> 26:47.664
There's always a way.
Just need a little help. That's all.

26:47.739 --> 26:52.335
You talkin' about Al?
I heard you talkin' to him last night.

26:52.410 --> 26:56.642
Just talkin' to myself.
Uh-uh. Folks talk different
when they talkin' to themselves.

26:56.715 --> 26:59.809
You was talkin' to somebody,
except they weren't there.

27:02.020 --> 27:05.615
- Al's kind of a friend of mine.
- He's the one told you aboutJake.

27:05.690 --> 27:08.124
Yep. Matter of fact, he did.

27:08.193 --> 27:10.320
And only you can see him.

27:10.395 --> 27:14.991
Me and... sometimes little kids
and animals too.

27:15.066 --> 27:19.628
You think Al likes snow?
I don't remember.
I don't think I ever asked him.

27:19.704 --> 27:23.800
I wanna see me some mountains,
some of them big ol' ones.

27:23.875 --> 27:28.335
The Rockies. Now, that sounds
like mountains, don't it?
Yes, it does.

27:28.413 --> 27:30.506
And some of those
big ol' trees.

27:30.582 --> 27:34.712
Redwoods.
Redwoods.

27:34.786 --> 27:38.847
Maybe find me someplace
with a lot of space,

27:38.923 --> 27:43.360
not too many people around,
you know, settle down.

27:43.428 --> 27:47.228
<i>[ Dog Barks ]</i>
You and Al could come visit.

27:47.298 --> 27:52.167
- That'd be nice. I'd like that.
- You two boys in love?

27:53.705 --> 27:58.608
<i>[ Insect Buzzing ]</i>
[ Prisoners Coughing ]

27:58.677 --> 28:01.168
I'm gonna kill him
if he put me back in that hole.

28:03.448 --> 28:09.353
I can't take it, Cole.
I can't.

28:14.192 --> 28:17.923
Hold still.
<i>All right. Get 'em fed</i>
<i>and get 'em to bed.</i>

28:17.996 --> 28:21.295
You men feed 'em,
put 'em down. Let's go.
Move it.

28:21.366 --> 28:23.994
[ Groaning ]
Come on.

28:24.069 --> 28:28.005
I hate to tell you this,
but Ziggy's got nothing new.
<i>Nada.</i> Zilch.

28:28.073 --> 28:30.200
Great. Great. Thanks.
You talkin' to Al?

28:30.275 --> 28:32.334
Yeah.
Can he hear me?

28:32.410 --> 28:34.674
No.

28:34.746 --> 28:39.740
Ask him if he'll come and visit.
[ Sam Groans ]

28:39.818 --> 28:45.120
Visit where?
Somewhere where there's mountains
and snow and trees and-

28:45.190 --> 28:47.784
Sure. Why not?
Sure. He'll come and visit you.

28:47.859 --> 28:51.295
- Oh, good.
- But first, we've gotta concentrate
on getting you out of here.

28:51.362 --> 28:54.957
Now, Ziggy has one idea-
It's a pretty good idea.

28:55.033 --> 28:58.264
What it is, you have
to predictJake's next robbery,

28:58.336 --> 29:01.965
and that way,
everything you say'll have more credibility,

29:02.040 --> 29:05.669
and maybe this Warden Elias
will believe you.
Okay.

29:05.744 --> 29:08.076
When's it gonna happen?

29:08.146 --> 29:10.808
When?
When's it gonna happen?
The next robbery?

29:10.882 --> 29:12.941
You want a when?
Al.

29:13.017 --> 29:16.783
Eight months.
Oh. Oh.

29:16.855 --> 29:21.189
- What did he say?
- He said thatJake Wiles is the key,

29:21.259 --> 29:25.423
but it's just gonna take
a little longer than we thought.

29:45.083 --> 29:50.919
Couldn't this wait till mornin'?
Annabelle thinks I'm sneakin' out
with some gal, leavin' this time of night.

29:50.989 --> 29:54.823
How'd that boy and Boone
find out about that jewelry store?

29:54.893 --> 29:57.953
And what about last night
in Kerrville?

29:58.029 --> 30:00.964
Hell. I don't know.
I had so much of that black crap...

30:01.032 --> 30:03.796
on my face that day in Langston,
I didn't recognize me.

30:03.868 --> 30:05.836
Ain't no way Boone could have.

30:05.904 --> 30:10.136
What about last night?
Now, you talked to somebody,
didn't you, boy?

30:10.208 --> 30:13.769
No. I- I ain't told nobody nothin',
Cooley.

30:13.845 --> 30:16.609
Why, that'd be real stupid.
Yeah, that would.

30:16.681 --> 30:20.674
If that boy knows about you,
then he just might know about me.

30:20.752 --> 30:24.745
I- I swear, Cooley,
I ain't told nobody nothin'.

30:24.823 --> 30:28.020
You get rid of that stuff
from Kerrville?
M-Most of it.

30:28.092 --> 30:33.428
I still got a couple of rings
and earrings left. Four thousand
is the best they give me for it.

30:33.498 --> 30:36.592
Yeah, well, I'm thinkin' maybe
we'd better back off a little...

30:36.668 --> 30:38.795
till things kind of settle down.

30:38.870 --> 30:42.863
That's a good idea, Cooley.
I been meaning to talk to you
about backin' off...

30:42.941 --> 30:45.933
j-just for a little while.

30:55.787 --> 30:59.120
Get up! Get up!
Where are you taking the boys
today, Cooley?

30:59.190 --> 31:01.624
We're gonna finish up that pipe
at Bellemeade Crossing.

31:01.693 --> 31:04.628
Swing by the Marion County turnoff
before you head over there.

31:04.696 --> 31:07.392
They got a stuck truck
loaded with peanut oil.

31:07.465 --> 31:10.628
I promised I'd get the boys
to dig her out.

31:10.702 --> 31:14.763
B.P., we're a week behind
on that Bellemeade trench.

31:14.839 --> 31:17.808
We ain't got time for no peanut truck.

31:19.744 --> 31:23.475
That crossing's been there
a long time, Cooley.
It ain't goin' nowhere.

31:24.649 --> 31:27.117
Or do you have some information
to the contrary?
No, sir.

31:27.185 --> 31:29.278
Then get to it!

31:30.755 --> 31:32.746
All right. Move it out!

31:45.503 --> 31:48.370
[ Guard Shouting, Indistinct ]

31:48.439 --> 31:51.567
Move it, damn it!
Takin' too much time!

31:51.643 --> 31:56.740
Sam, Ziggy says that your best bet
is to try and bribe someone
to get the information outside.

31:56.814 --> 31:58.782
With what?
With what?

31:58.850 --> 32:00.215
Yeah.
With what?

32:00.285 --> 32:04.779
Uh, we're workin' on that.
We're workin' on that " with what.''
Hold it! Hold it! Hold it!

32:04.856 --> 32:07.290
What?
Damn it. It's diggin' in deeper.

32:08.493 --> 32:11.792
We're gonna have to build up
under where that other tire's spinnin'.

32:11.863 --> 32:16.425
Hey, Cole, find me a log or a rock
or somethin' to put under that tire.
<i>No.!</i>

32:16.501 --> 32:18.662
Well, I ain't gonna
let him out of my sight, Cooley!

32:18.736 --> 32:21.728
I said no, damn it!
All right. Okay.
All right.

32:21.806 --> 32:25.469
Cole, come on back here right now.

32:30.081 --> 32:32.345
Son of a-

32:32.417 --> 32:37.081
Hey! Hey, it's Jake Wiles down here!
Someone's shot him all to hell!

32:38.756 --> 32:42.886
Hey, Boone, get back here, boy.
I'll throw you in the pit, Boone.

32:42.961 --> 32:46.226
- <i>I told you to get back here.</i>
<i>When I talk,you better listen.</i>
- I'll kill you!

32:47.298 --> 32:50.825
No! Boone! Get off him!
Come on!

32:53.771 --> 32:57.138
Boy, you just earned yourself
another trip to the pit.

32:57.208 --> 32:59.472
I ain't never goin'
in that pit again!

32:59.544 --> 33:02.672
Well, it's either that or a cockfight
with your friend Cole here.

33:06.317 --> 33:10.014
- I'll take the fight.
- You got it.

33:10.088 --> 33:13.080
All right.
<i>[ Prisoners Chattering ]</i>

33:16.227 --> 33:19.663
Sam, a " cockfight''
is Southern prison slang...

33:19.731 --> 33:23.258
for a fight between two prisoners...
to the death.

33:23.334 --> 33:26.929
Come on. Get up, boy.
Come on.

33:31.342 --> 33:34.243
Put 'em in separate trucks.

33:34.312 --> 33:38.373
Go on the radio,
call the sheriff and tell him
to get on over here with the coroner.

33:39.450 --> 33:43.250
<i>[ Guard ]</i>
<i>Let's go. Let's go.</i>
<i>Sam, I don't get it.</i>

33:43.321 --> 33:46.779
I mean, it doesn't fit-
What's this goon lookin' at?

33:48.559 --> 33:52.120
Jake was supposed
to rob four more jewelry stores.

33:52.196 --> 33:56.030
- He's gonna have a little trouble
doin' it right now.
- <i>Hey, Cooley, look at this.!</i>

33:56.100 --> 33:59.558
There's gotta be
a couple thousand dollars here.
I'll be damned if the grocery business...

33:59.637 --> 34:01.798
isn't something I oughta
look into!

34:01.873 --> 34:05.434
Put that on back
and let the sheriff find it.

34:05.510 --> 34:07.876
<i>Well, I guess</i>
<i>that rules out robbery.</i>

34:07.945 --> 34:11.813
Which leaves
only 999 other motives.
That's true.

34:11.882 --> 34:15.545
I gotta fight that guy to the death.
I mean, he's quicker
than greased lightning.

34:15.620 --> 34:19.454
- You saw at the barn,
I was lucky 'cause he wasn't-
- <i>[ Al ] Don't worry.</i>

34:19.524 --> 34:22.219
Don't worry, Sam.
I'll figure something out somehow.

34:22.293 --> 34:26.661
Jake's murder was never solved,
but somehow you changed history,
and Jake got killed.

34:26.731 --> 34:29.996
I know that, Al.
Look, what we don't-

34:30.068 --> 34:34.094
What?
Most murder victims are killed
by people that they know, right?

34:34.172 --> 34:36.766
Uh, right.
Right?

34:36.841 --> 34:39.002
Who would have the best reason
to killJake?

34:39.077 --> 34:42.478
Ooh!
Does he have any ex-wives?
A partner.

34:42.547 --> 34:46.483
Huh?
A partner who doesn't
trustJake anymore.

34:46.551 --> 34:49.315
A partner who's afraid thatJake
is gonna expose him.

34:49.387 --> 34:53.847
Oh, a partner who got scared yesterday
when a certain inmate said...

34:53.925 --> 34:56.792
that he knew about the robbery
that happened the other night.

34:56.860 --> 34:59.125
Uh-huh.

34:59.197 --> 35:03.133
I'll put my money
on goon-meister there.

35:04.435 --> 35:09.338
I agree. Only the way things
have been going, I don't think
we're gonna be able to nail him.

35:12.276 --> 35:15.245
We're gonna have to escape.

35:20.551 --> 35:24.749
[ Chattering, Laughing ]

35:29.160 --> 35:32.288
[ Guard ]
Whoo!
[ Guards Chattering ]

35:32.363 --> 35:36.800
We're all gonna do that.
That's right. It's time
to have some fun now.

35:37.835 --> 35:40.269
<i>Move it along.!</i>
<i>Get 'em, Cooley.!</i>

35:40.338 --> 35:42.898
<i>[ Chatter Continues ]</i>

35:44.408 --> 35:47.639
<i>Come on.! Let's move it along</i>
<i>and have some fun tonight, boys.!</i>

35:47.712 --> 35:50.340
<i>It's party time.!</i>
<i>Come on.! Move it out.!</i>

35:50.414 --> 35:52.905
<i>Bring 'em in.</i>

35:57.188 --> 36:01.921
All right.
Hold your arms out.

36:03.094 --> 36:06.359
- You right-handed, Boone?
- Yeah.

36:06.430 --> 36:09.160
Well, this'll even it up,

36:11.269 --> 36:14.432
keep you two lovebirds happy.

36:14.505 --> 36:17.770
<i>Now, if y'all ain't never...</i>

36:17.842 --> 36:20.777
seen no cockfight,
here's the rules.

36:20.845 --> 36:25.339
<i>Number one:</i>
<i>Ain't no helpin'the contestants.</i>

36:25.416 --> 36:29.182
Sam, Ziggy still doesn't have a line
on how you escape. The best
we could think of...

36:29.253 --> 36:31.244
is you gotta think
of some kind of distraction.

36:31.322 --> 36:34.587
- The chains don't come off
till one of these boys is dead.
- <i>[ Men ] Yeah.</i>

36:34.659 --> 36:40.393
- Yeah.
- Y'all got any final last words?

36:40.464 --> 36:42.523
Is that what you said
toJake before you shot him?

36:42.600 --> 36:45.694
Too bad you ain't gonna
live long enough to regret that, boy.

36:47.271 --> 36:50.934
- <i>Give 'em the chains.</i>
<i>Get 'em ready.</i>
- <i>[ Man ] Come on.!</i>

36:53.277 --> 36:55.609
Oh, I don't like this.
I don't like this.

36:55.680 --> 36:58.080
<i>[ Onlookers Clamoring ]</i>

36:59.317 --> 37:01.410
Quiet!

37:01.485 --> 37:04.079
I ain't goin' back in there.

37:04.155 --> 37:06.715
All right! Go get 'em, boys!
Get in and fight!

37:08.726 --> 37:10.751
[ Clamoring Continues ]

37:21.973 --> 37:25.807
Boone- Boone,
this is our chance to escape.
Do you hear me?

37:25.876 --> 37:29.107
Cooley's not gonna let you live
even if ya kill me.

37:29.180 --> 37:33.617
He's afraid you're gonna connect
him with Wiles.

37:33.684 --> 37:36.175
- He's a flake candy-ass!
- [ Gasps ]

37:36.254 --> 37:41.419
Your only chance is to trust me.
When I say " go,'' get ready to go.

37:44.061 --> 37:46.154
No! No!

37:53.537 --> 37:56.005
- Moccasin!
- [ All Yelping ]

37:57.742 --> 38:00.108
[ Gunshots ]

38:03.014 --> 38:05.244
Damn it to hell.

38:05.316 --> 38:08.717
Monroe! Monroe!
Get over here!

38:08.786 --> 38:11.949
Spread out.
We gotta find 'em.

38:12.023 --> 38:15.390
Let's head for the trucks.
Yeah.

38:20.097 --> 38:22.861
<i>[ Bird Calling ]</i>

38:26.837 --> 38:29.897
- <i>[ Sam ]</i>
<i>Let's get up to that truck, Boone.</i>
- <i>[ Owl Hooting ]</i>

38:29.974 --> 38:33.034
Come on.

38:42.987 --> 38:46.980
No, no, no, no. Wait, wait, wait.
Any minute now,
they're gonna know we're here.

38:47.058 --> 38:50.152
Sam, that was incredible.
You made Houdini look like a piker.

38:50.227 --> 38:53.196
Wait a second. Wait a second.
Get the gas cap. Take it off.

38:54.965 --> 38:57.798
Here. Good, good, good.

38:59.070 --> 39:02.437
<i>Perfect.! Incredible idea.!</i>

39:04.975 --> 39:06.738
Go!

39:15.619 --> 39:18.952
Holy damnation!
Monroe!

39:19.023 --> 39:23.357
<i>Monroe, the truck.!</i>
<i>Over there.!</i>

39:25.796 --> 39:28.526
[ All Shouting ]
Get the dogs!

39:28.599 --> 39:32.592
Get the dogs!
Get the dogs!

39:41.445 --> 39:44.073
Over there.
[ Indistinct ]

39:46.117 --> 39:48.085
Over here.

39:48.152 --> 39:53.886
Here, dogs!
Dog food right this way!
[ Dogs Barking ]

40:19.183 --> 40:22.084
[ Sam Grunting ]
<i>[ Dog Growling ]</i>

40:22.153 --> 40:26.021
- <i>Well, well, well.</i>
- [ Gun Cocks ]

40:26.090 --> 40:29.423
Get on over here.
I said, get on over here.

40:29.493 --> 40:34.897
<i>[ Dog Continues Growling ]</i>
<i>You boys make myjob real easy.</i>

40:34.965 --> 40:37.832
<i>Two dangerous escaped prisoners</i>
<i>heading for the state line.</i>

40:37.902 --> 40:42.271
- I might even end up
with a commendation out of it.
- Least we won't get shot in the back likeJake.

40:42.339 --> 40:45.672
Loose lips sink ships.
<i>[ Dog Growls ]</i>

40:45.743 --> 40:48.007
I just don't know what he'd be doin'
tellin' ya what he's doin'.

40:49.079 --> 40:51.013
- He didn't.
- What do you mean?

40:51.081 --> 40:54.107
- Hey. Hey, you stupid mutt, over here!
- [ Dog Barking ]

40:55.352 --> 40:58.219
[ Yelling ]

41:00.958 --> 41:03.791
Sam, he smashed his head
down there.

41:07.198 --> 41:09.758
[ Both Panting, Grunting ]

41:12.770 --> 41:16.501
- [ Sam ] He's dead.
- <i>[ Boone ]</i>
<i>Yeah. Better him than us.</i>

41:16.574 --> 41:19.668
Al, how far
to the state line?

41:19.743 --> 41:24.146
Uh- Uh, 20 miles.
Go straight upstream.

41:25.649 --> 41:29.745
Come on.
We got some traveling to do.

41:29.820 --> 41:31.811
Let's go.

41:35.159 --> 41:39.061
Sam, this is it right here.
The Louisiana state line
right at the top of the hill.

41:39.129 --> 41:42.895
Ziggy says all Boone has to do is get out
of the state, and he's home free.
This is it.

41:45.803 --> 41:48.966
Louisiana's on the other side
of that hill. We made it.

41:51.342 --> 41:54.175
Which way you headed?
I don't know.

41:54.245 --> 41:57.840
I don't know.
Me neither.

42:03.754 --> 42:05.745
Thanks.

42:05.823 --> 42:09.418
Anytime. Get goin'.
Go on.

42:11.996 --> 42:14.692
You take care!

42:16.333 --> 42:19.769
What's gonna happen
to him, Al?

42:19.837 --> 42:22.806
He disappears
into the fabric of society,

42:22.873 --> 42:27.810
but in three years,
a man fitting his description
is spotted in Washington state...

42:27.878 --> 42:30.745
working for the forestry service.

42:30.814 --> 42:33.180
In the mountains
with the big trees. Yeah.
Mmm.

42:33.250 --> 42:37.152
And you disappear too-
I mean, Cole disappears too.

42:37.221 --> 42:41.521
In fact, after a couple of years,
they give up lookin' for either one
of you.

42:41.592 --> 42:47.189
Oh, you'll be interested
in this. Work Prison
Number 1 1 is shut down...

42:47.264 --> 42:50.290
three months after you guys escape.
[ Sighs ]

42:51.302 --> 42:55.466
Hey! Hey.

42:55.539 --> 42:58.736
Tell Al good-bye for me.

42:58.809 --> 43:01.778
He can hear ya.

43:01.845 --> 43:04.245
Thanks, Al.

43:09.553 --> 43:12.784
Thanks, Al.
Bye, Sam.

43:23.634 --> 43:26.330
<i>[ Sam Narrating ]</i>
<i>Quantum leaping through time,</i>
<i>I've leapt into an electric chair,</i>

43:26.403 --> 43:29.804
<i>gunfights and a variety</i>
<i>ofhandcuffs.</i>

43:29.873 --> 43:32.239
<i>It looks like</i>
<i>I finally raided a cushy time.</i>

43:32.309 --> 43:34.539
Thank you.

43:34.612 --> 43:38.639
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>No. Thank you.</i>

43:45.289 --> 43:48.918
Good morning, tiger.
Good morning.

43:48.993 --> 43:51.587
[ Chuckling ]
Oh, no, no. You gotta
stop doing that.

43:51.662 --> 43:54.460
You want me to stop?
No. Yes, please.

43:54.531 --> 43:57.295
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Mom? My God, Mom.</i>

43:57.368 --> 44:00.428
What would Dad say?

44:00.504 --> 44:02.472
Oh, boy.

